text: Mohammed Mzali (, 23 December 1925 - 23 June 2010) was a Tunisian politician. He served as Prime Minister of Tunisia from 23 April 1980 through 8 July 1986. Mzali was born in Monastir, Tunisia. He served as a member of the International Olympic Committee from 1965 until his death in 2010. Mzali died in Paris, France from a long-illness, aged 85.Former Tunisian Premier Mohamed Mzali, International Olympic Committe member, dies at 85 Fox News, 24 June 2010. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:1925 births Category:2010 deaths Category:Prime Ministers of Tunisia Category:International Olympic Committee
